sources.title: Crashing Thru (1939) RENFREW OF THE ROYAL MOUNTED
sources.description:
Stars: James Newill, Warren Hull, Jean Carmen
 Director: Elmer Clifton

 Six people are in on a gold robbery. Three of them double-cross the others. Mountie Renfrew has to go after them alone when his partner Kelly is wounded.

metadata.Plot: Canadian Mountd Sergeant Renfrew (James Newill) and Corporal Kelly (Warren Hull) are on the way to their Post from Headquarters when the small steamer on which they are traveling is held up. Helpless to stop the thieves from getting away with a gold shipment, they immediately take up the chase when they are freed. They also clear Ann Chambers (Jean Carmen) and her brother, Fred Chambers (Dave O'Brien), of any involvement with the robbery.
metadata.Writer: Sherman L. Lowe, Laurie York Erskine
metadata.Actors: James Newill, Jean Carmen, Warren Hull
